        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 4:30PM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM CDT, the public reported a strong thunderstorm near Alda,
or 10 miles southwest of Grand Island, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Alda around 435 PM CDT.
Grand Island around 440 PM CDT.

This includes Interstate 80 between mile markers 300 and 327.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
